{"id":87853,"title":"Elbow fractures and dislocations.","abstract":"Elbow fractures are common in pediatric patients. Most injuries to the pediatric elbow are stable and require simple immobilization; however, more severe fractures can occur, often requiring operative stabilization and/or close monitoring. This article highlights the common fractures and dislocations about the pediatric elbow and discusses the history, evaluation, and treatment options for specific injuries. ","date":"2014-06-30","categories":"Wounds and Injuries","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24975761","annotations":[{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.28316,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Elbow","weight":0.139198,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elbow"},{"name":"Pediatrics","weight":0.123825,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pediatrics"},{"name":"Evaluation","weight":0.0727855,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evaluation"},{"name":"Dislocation","weight":0.023431,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dislocation"},{"name":"Glossary of professional wrestling terms","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glossary_of_professional_wrestling_terms"},{"name":"Option (finance)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Option_(finance)"},{"name":"Clarification and stabilization of wine","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clarification_and_stabilization_of_wine"},{"name":"History","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History"}]}
